;</a> <span class=\"fn\">n</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/Basic.html#PowerSeries.coeff\">PowerSeries.coeff</a> <span class=\"fn\">n</span>)</span> (<span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">p</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/WellKnown.html#PowerSeries.invOneSubPow\">PowerSeries.invOneSubPow</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span> <span class=\"fn\">d</span>)</span></span>)</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Polynomial/Eval/Defs.html#Polynomial.eval\">eval</a> <span class=\"fn\">(↑<span class=\"fn\">n</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">p</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Polynomial/HilbertPoly.html#Polynomial.hilbertPoly\">hilbertPoly</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">d</span>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The key property of Hilbert polynomials. If `F` is a field with characteristic `0`, `p : F[X]` and\n`d : ℕ`, then for any large enough `n : ℕ`, `(Polynomial.hilbertPoly p d).eval (n : F)` equals the\ncoefficient of `Xⁿ` in the power series expansion of `p/(1 - X)ᵈ`.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Polynomial/HilbertPoly.html#Polynomial.coeff_mul_invOneSubPow_eq_hilbertPoly_eval","kind":"theorem","line":161,"name":"Polynomial.coeff_mul_invOneSubPow_eq_hilbertPoly_eval","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/RingTheory/Polynomial/HilbertPoly.lean#L161-L190"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">noncomputable def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Polynomial/HilbertPoly.html#Polynomial.hilbertPoly_linearMap\"><span class=\"name\">Polynomial</span>.<span class=\"name\">hilbertPoly_linearMap</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">F</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#Field\">Field</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">d</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Polynomial/Basic.html#Polynomial\">Polynomial</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Module/LinearMap/Defs.html#LinearMap\">→ₗ[</a><span class=\"fn\">F</span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Module/LinearMap/Defs.html#LinearMap\">]</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Polynomial/Basic.html#Polynomial\">Polynomial</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The function that sends any `p : F[X]` to `Polynomial.hilbertPoly p d` is an `F`-linear map from\n`F[X]` to `F[X]`.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Polynomial/HilbertPoly.html#Polynomial.hilbertPoly_linearMap","kind":"def","line":150,"name":"Polynomial.hilbertPoly_linearMap","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/RingTheory/Polynomial/HilbertPoly.lean#L150-L157"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Polynomial/HilbertPoly.html#Polynomial.hilbertPoly_smul\"><span class=\"name\">Polynomial</span>.<span class=\"name\">hilbertPoly_smul</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">F</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span 