85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/RingTheory/Polynomial/HilbertPoly.lean#L119-L119"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Polynomial/HilbertPoly.html#Polynomial.hilbertPoly_zero_left\"><span class=\"name\">Polynomial</span>.<span class=\"name\">hilbertPoly_zero_left</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">F</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#Field\">Field</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">d</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Polynomial/HilbertPoly.html#Polynomial.hilbertPoly\">hilbertPoly</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span> <span class=\"fn\">d</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Polynomial/HilbertPoly.html#Polynomial.hilbertPoly_zero_left","kind":"theorem","line":114,"name":"Polynomial.hilbertPoly_zero_left","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/RingTheory/Polynomial/HilbertPoly.lean#L114-L117"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">noncomputable def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Polynomial/HilbertPoly.html#Polynomial.hilbertPoly\"><span class=\"name\">Polynomial</span>.<span class=\"name\">hilbertPoly</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">F</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#Field\">Field</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">p</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Polynomial/Basic.html#Polynomial\">Polynomial</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">d</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Polynomial/Basic.html#Polynomial\">Polynomial</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`Polynomial.hilbertPoly p 0 = 0`; for any `d : ℕ`, `Polynomial.hilbertPoly p (d + 1)`\nis defined as `∑ i ∈ p.support, (p.coeff i) • Polynomial.preHilbertPoly F d i`. If\n`M` is a graded module whose Poincaré series can be written as `p(X)/(1 - X)ᵈ` for some\n`p : ℚ[X]` with integer coefficients, then `Polynomial.hilbertPoly p d` is the Hilbert\npolynomial of `M`. See also `Polynomial.coeff_mul_invOneSubPow_eq_hilbertPoly_eval`,\nwhich says that `PowerSeries.coeff F n (p * PowerSeries.invOneSubPow F d)` equals\n`(Polynomial.hilbertPoly p d).eval (n : F)` for any large enough `n : ℕ`.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Polynomial/HilbertPoly.html#Polynomial.hilbertPoly","kind":"def","line":101,"name":"Polynomial.hilbertPoly","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/RingTheory/Polynomial/HilbertPoly.lean#L101-L112"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Polynomial/HilbertPoly.html#Polynomial.preHilbertPoly_eq_choose_sub_add\"><span class=\"name\">Polynomial</span>.<span class=\"name\">preHilbertPoly_eq_choose_sub_add</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">F</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#Field\">Field</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/CharZero/Defs.html#CharZero\">CharZero</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">d</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">k </span><span class=\"fn\">n</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hkn</span> : <span class=\"fn\">k</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\">n</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Polynomial/Eval/Defs.html#Polynomial.eval\">eval</a> <span class=\"fn\">(↑<span class=\"fn\">n</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Polynomial/HilbertPoly.html#Polynomial.preHilbertPoly\">preHilbertPoly</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span> <span class=\"fn\">d</span> <span class=\"fn\">k</span>)</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">n</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HSub.hSub\">-</a> <span class=\"fn\">k</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HAdd.hAdd\">+</a> <span class=\"fn\">d</span>).<a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Nat/Choose/Basic.html#Nat.choose\">choose</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">d</span>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Polynomial/HilbertPoly.html#Polynomial.preHilbertPoly_eq_choose_sub_add","kind":"theorem","line":90,"name":"Polynomial.preHilbertPoly_eq_choose_sub_add","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/RingTheory/Polynomial/HilbertPoly.lean#L90-L97"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Polynomial/HilbertPoly.html#Polynomial.leadingCoeff_preHilbertPoly\"><span class=\"name\">Polynomial</span>.<span class=\"name\">leadingCoeff_preHilbertPoly</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">F</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#Field\">Field</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/CharZero/Defs.html#CharZero\">CharZero</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">d </span><span class=\"fn\">k</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Polynomial/HilbertPoly.html#Polynomial.preHilbertPoly\">preHilbertPoly</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span> <span class=\"fn\">d</span> <span class=\"fn\">k</span>)</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Polynomial/Degree/Defs.html#Polynomial.leadingCoeff\">leadingCoeff</a></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">(↑<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">d</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Nat/Factorial/Basic.html#Nat.factorial\">factorial</a></span>)</span><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Inv.inv\">⁻¹</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Polynomial/HilbertPoly.html#Polynomial.leadingCoeff_preHilbertPoly","kind":"theorem","line":86,"name":"Polynomial.leadingCoeff_preHilbertPoly","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/RingTheory/Polynomial/HilbertPoly.lean#L86-L88"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Polynomial/HilbertPoly.html#Polynomial.coeff_preHilbertPoly_self\"><span class=\"name\">Polynomial</span>.<span class=\"name\">coeff_preHilbertPoly_self</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">F</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#Field\">Field</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/CharZero/Defs.html#CharZero\">CharZero</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">d </span><span class=\"fn\">k</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Polynomial/HilbertPoly.html#Polynomial.preHilbertPoly\">preHilbertPoly</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span> <span class=\"fn\">d</span> <span class=\"fn\">k</span>)</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Polynomial/Basic.html#Polynomial.coeff\">coeff</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">d</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">(↑<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">d</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Nat/Factorial/Basic.html#Nat.factorial\">factorial</a></span>)</span><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Inv.inv\">⁻¹</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Polynomial/HilbertPoly.html#Polynomial.coeff_preHilbertPoly_self","kind":"theorem","line":72,"name":"Polynomial.coeff_preHilbertPoly_self","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/RingTheory/Polynomial/HilbertPoly.lean#L72-L84"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Polynomial/HilbertPoly.html#Polynomial.natDegree_preHilbertPoly\"><span class=\"name\">Polynomial</span>.<span class=\"name\">natDegree_preHilbertPoly</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">F</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#Field\">Field</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/CharZero/Defs.html#CharZero\">CharZero</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">d </span><span class=\"fn\">k</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Polynomial/HilbertPoly.html#Polynomial.preHilbertPoly\">preHilbertPoly</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span> <span class=\"fn\">d</span> <span class=\"fn\">k</span>)</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Polynomial/Degree/Defs.html#Polynomial.natDegree\">natDegree</a></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">d</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Polynomial/HilbertPoly.html#Polynomial.natDegree_preHilbertPoly","kind":"theorem","line":66,"name":"Polynomial.natDegree_preHilbertPoly","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/RingTheory/Polynomial/HilbertPoly.lean#L66-L70"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">noncomputable def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Polynomial/HilbertPoly.html#Polynomial.preHilbertPoly\"><span class=\"name\">Polynomial</span>.<span class=\"name\">preHilbertPoly</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">F</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#Field\">Field</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">d </span><span class=\"fn\">k</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Polynomial/Basic.html#Polynomial\">Polynomial</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"For any field `F` and natural numbers `d` and `k`, `Polynomial.preHilbertPoly F d k`\nis defined as `(d.factorial : F)⁻¹ • ((ascPochhammer F d).comp (X - (C (k : F)) + 1))`.\nThis is the most basic form of Hilbert polynomials. `Polynomial.preHilbertPoly ℚ d 0`\nis exactly the Hilbert polynomial of the polynomial ring `ℚ[X_0,...,X_d]` viewed as\na graded module over itself. In fact, `Polynomial.preHilbertPoly F d k` is the\nsame as `Polynomial.hilbertPoly ((X : F[X]) ^ k) (d + 1)` for any field `F` and\n`d k : ℕ` (see the lemma `Polynomial.hilbertPoly_X_pow_succ`). See also the lemma\n`Polynomial.preHilbertPoly_eq_choose_sub_add`, which states that if `CharZero F`,\nthen for any `d k n : ℕ` with `k ≤ n`, `(Polynomial.preHilbertPoly F d k).eval (n : F)`\nequals `(n - k + d).choose d`.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Polynomial/HilbertPoly.html#Polynomial.preHilbertPoly","kind":"def","line":51,"name":"Polynomial.preHilbertPoly","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/RingTheory/Polynomial/HilbertPoly.lean#L51-L64"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Algebra.Polynomial.AlgebraMap","Mathlib.Algebra.Polynomial.Eval.SMul","Mathlib.Algebra.Polynomial.Roots","Mathlib.Order.Interval.Set.Infinite","Mathlib.RingTheory.Polynomial.Pochhammer","Mathlib.RingTheory.PowerSeries.WellKnown","Mathlib.Tactic.FieldSimp","Mathlib.Algebra.NoZeroSMulDivisors.Basic"],"instances":[],"name":"Mathlib.RingTheory.Polynomial.HilbertPoly"}